Class Hash

java.lang.Object
  Hash

public class Hash
extends java.lang.Object

Hash class contains methods Hash, createTable, printTableand isHash functions create a hashtable, print out a hash table, return loadFactor and collisions

Author:

Constructor Summary
Hash()
          constructor for hash, initializes tableSize to 37, hashTable to an array of ObjectList's (then initalizes all the lists) sets collisions to 0, occupied to 0, buckets to 0, loadFactor to 0.00 (double)
 
Method Summary
 void createTable(java.util.Scanner inFile)
          createTable takes in argument inFile which contains the hashTable text file, reads in each word(adding delims for spaces in case user accidentally adds them to the text file, applies the hash function to each String(word) to get a value from 0 to 36, checks to see if that spot is occupied in the hash table, if it is the occupied variable is incremented and the collision is resolved by chaining via linked lists by added the word to the end of the list.
 boolean isHash(java.lang.String s)
          isHash takes in a String s, and calls the getHash function by passing the string if the index (represented by the return integer value from getHash) of the hashArray containeds the same String a true value is returned, if the String is not contained in the hashTable, false is returned.
 void printTable(java.io.PrintWriter pw)
          printTable method prints a formatted list of the HashTable contained in the Hash Class while traversing through the hashTable array, each index is checked for certain parameters, if empty the array index is skipped, if the size is greater than 1, a reference to the first node in the array index list is created and traversed through until null, printing the strings held by the nodes in the list, if the size is 1 the string held by the first node is printed

Method Detail

createTable

public void createTable(java.util.Scanner inFile)
createTable takes in argument inFile which contains the hashTable text file, reads in each word(adding delims for spaces in case user accidentally adds them to the text file, applies the hash function to each String(word) to get a value from 0 to 36, checks to see if that spot is occupied in the hash table, if it is the occupied variable is incremented and the collision is resolved by chaining via linked lists by added the word to the end of the list.

Parameters:
Scanner - inFile contains the hashWords.txt reference, read in to the table

isHash

public boolean isHash(java.lang.String s)
isHash takes in a String s, and calls the getHash function by passing the string if the index (represented by the return integer value from getHash) of the hashArray containeds the same String a true value is returned, if the String is not contained in the hashTable, false is returned.

Parameters:
String - s, passed to getHash to get hashValue for the array table
Returns:
boolean true of false

printTable

public void printTable(java.io.PrintWriter pw)
                throws java.io.IOException
printTable method prints a formatted list of the HashTable contained in the Hash Class while traversing through the hashTable array, each index is checked for certain parameters, if empty the array index is skipped, if the size is greater than 1, a reference to the first node in the array index list is created and traversed through until null, printing the strings held by the nodes in the list, if the size is 1 the string held by the first node is printed

Parameters:
PrintWriter - pw - used for printing a formatted table Index for the hash words
Throws:
java.io.IOException
